Next time you&#x27;re in a conversation about language design and someone sighs, shakes their head and tells you that sad legacy design choices are just the burden of the past and we&#x27;re helpless to avoid repeating them, try to remember that this is not so.&quot;<p>I think rust is neat, but this is somewhat arrogant.<p>Rust is <i>amazingly young</i>.  10-20 years from now, when rust hopefully has bajillions of users, if this is still true, <i>then</i> you can say it.
I mean, do you really believe that Rust won&#x27;t have things that turn out to be warts from 1.0 it can&#x27;t remove 10-20 years from now?
